<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Ketteler</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-07"><hi rend="italic">July 7,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. von Holleben’s note of
                            May 14, I have the honor to inform you in accordance with instructions
                            received that Mr. Greiner, chancellor of the German consulate at Sydney,
                            who has been provisionally designated to act as the German member of the
                            Samoan land commission, has arrived at Apia, and that he entered upon
                            the duties of the office on the 1st of April of this year.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ketteler.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>